 show aesthetics; the social significance of 'games'; 'ordinary' people as television performers, and questions of quiz show reception (from interactivity to on-line fandom).Key FeaturesRepresents one of few book-length studies of the quiz showOffers an accessible introduction to the genre for undergraduate studentsDraws upon new archival research in order to contribute to knowledge about the early history of the quiz showDemonstrates why the quiz show matters to Television StudiesBrings together key approaches in the field with new interventions and areas of study (such as the quiz show in the multi-platform age, and the study of 'ordinary' people as performers)."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Television / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748631575zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748631575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748631575/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK